    A partially specified check about an approximate relationship to a double[] subject using a tolerance.

      • of

        public void of(double... expected)
        Fails if the values in the subject were expected to be within the tolerance of the given values but were not or if they were expected not to be within the tolerance but were. The subject and tolerance are specified earlier in the fluent call chain.

      • ofElementsIn

        public abstract void ofElementsIn(Iterable<? extends Number> expected)
        Fails if the values in the subject were expected to be within the tolerance of the given values but were not or if they were expected not to be within the tolerance but were. The subject and tolerance are specified earlier in the fluent call chain. The values will be cast to doubles if necessary, which might lose precision.
